34:43.164 --> 34:45.667
<i>I got to get on the</i>
<i>second blade right now.</i>

34:45.667 --> 34:47.335
<i>I can't afford</i>
<i>any more mistakes.</i>

34:47.335 --> 34:49.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:49.796 --> 34:51.172
<i>It's go time,</i>
<i>I got to get it done.</i>

34:51.172 --> 34:53.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:53.091 --> 34:54.884
<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

34:54.884 --> 34:56.678
<i>- So now that I'm done</i>
<i>profiling my blade,</i>

34:56.678 --> 34:58.888
<i>and getting the saw</i>
<i>into the spine,</i>

34:58.888 --> 35:03.560
<i>I'm ready, but not ready,</i>
<i>to quench this blade.</i>

35:03.560 --> 35:05.270
I am nervous as heck.

35:05.270 --> 35:06.896
I'm going to
normalize the blade.

35:06.896 --> 35:09.524
Reduce the stress in the
steel, refine the grain.

35:09.524 --> 35:11.610
Hopefully make it
as straight as possible,

35:11.610 --> 35:13.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:13.778 --> 35:17.365
<i>I'm quenching my blade now,</i>
<i>and if it fails, I'm out.</i>

35:17.365 --> 35:18.950
<i>There's no way</i>
<i>I'm going to have time</i>

35:18.950 --> 35:20.285
<i>to make another blade.</i>

35:20.285 --> 35:23.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:23.955 --> 35:27.000
I don't hear any cracks.
I didn't hear any pings.

35:27.000 --> 35:29.586
I'm not sure if it's hard yet,
but it's at least in one piece.

35:29.586 --> 35:31.504
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:31.504 --> 35:34.716
Oh, yeah,
that is a good sound.

35:34.716 --> 35:36.801
[laughs]

35:36.801 --> 35:38.637
I'm happy now.

35:38.637 --> 35:41.514
It's all easy peasy
lemon squeezy

35:41.514 --> 35:45.477
from here on out, I think.
Hopefully, I don't jinx myself.

35:45.477 --> 35:47.062
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:47.062 --> 35:49.147
<i>- Yesterday</i>
<i>was a total fiasco.</i>

35:49.147 --> 35:51.775
<i>I discovered cracks</i>
<i>in my first blade,</i>

35:51.775 --> 35:53.652
<i>uh, so I had to immediately</i>

35:53.652 --> 35:55.570
<i>forge out a new blade,</i>
<i>which I did.</i>

35:55.570 --> 35:57.155
<i>First thing this morning,</i>

35:57.155 --> 36:00.200
<i>we did a heat treat,</i>
<i>and it worked.</i>

36:00.200 --> 36:03.119
<i>So I'm getting ready</i>
<i>to cast a bronze bow guard.</i>

36:03.119 --> 36:07.499
<i>My frame is set up, I got my</i>
<i>bronze melting in my forge.</i>

36:07.499 --> 36:10.001
I never anticipated having
quite this many problems

36:10.001 --> 36:11.711
<i>on this sawback sword...</i>

36:11.711 --> 36:14.464
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

36:14.464 --> 36:15.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:15.840 --> 36:18.218
<i>but we got a good pour.</i>

36:18.218 --> 36:21.680
<i>I got a blade over there.</i>
<i>I have a guard that I like.</i>

36:21.680 --> 36:25.558
<i>I have my handle wood cut out.</i>
<i>I have my thumb guard cut out.</i>

36:25.558 --> 36:27.644
I got my rear quillion

36:27.644 --> 36:30.480
integrated into this
D-guard.

36:30.480 --> 36:33.149
So actually, I'm sitting
really, really well.

36:33.149 --> 36:34.693
<i>[groovy music]</i>

36:34.693 --> 36:37.028
- Day five,
I'm mentally exhausted.

36:37.028 --> 36:38.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:38.947 --> 36:41.825
So I get the handle and the
guard fit to the tang,

36:41.825 --> 36:45.286
and it's pretty snug,
but I screwed the pommel on,

36:45.286 --> 36:47.330
<i>and there's a gap.</i>

36:47.330 --> 36:49.916
<i>And I'm like, where the hell</i>
<i>did that come from?</i>

36:49.916 --> 36:51.584
It wasn't there a minute ago.

36:51.584 --> 36:54.504
I'm trying to add
these brass spacers

36:54.504 --> 36:56.756
to help me
get the spacing I need

36:56.756 --> 36:58.675
between my handle
and guard and everything.

36:58.675 --> 36:59.926
[sighs]

36:59.926 --> 37:02.721
What the frick happened?

37:02.721 --> 37:05.098
<i>I'm trying to get it</i>
<i>as good as I can get it.</i>

37:05.098 --> 37:07.183
<i>Holy [bleep].</i>

37:07.183 --> 37:09.227
This was a hell of a challenge.

37:09.227 --> 37:12.230
<i>I really didn't think</i>
<i>that I was going to make it,</i>

37:12.230 --> 37:14.816
<i>but I got it finished</i>
<i>in the last minute.</i>

37:14.816 --> 37:16.526
Yay.

37:16.526 --> 37:19.446
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:19.446 --> 37:21.156
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:21.156 --> 37:23.324
- Trevor, Devin,
welcome back to The Forge.

37:23.324 --> 37:25.160
You've had five days
at your home forges

37:25.160 --> 37:26.911
to work on your finale weapons.

37:26.911 --> 37:30.123
Trevor, how did it go?
- It went pretty good.

37:30.123 --> 37:32.709
It was long days;
a lot of hard work.

37:32.709 --> 37:37.005
<i>It's a 115-layer Damascus,</i>
<i>three steels.</i>

37:37.005 --> 37:38.965
<i>The guard is constructed</i>
<i>out of steel</i>

37:38.965 --> 37:40.800
<i>I had left over</i>
<i>from the blade.</i>

37:40.800 --> 37:44.137
- Great, Devin, tell the judges
about your blade.

37:44.137 --> 37:45.597
- Unfortunately,
it's the second blade I made.

37:45.597 --> 37:47.056
The first one developed
a lot of cracks.

37:47.056 --> 37:48.767
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:48.767 --> 37:52.020
<i>I used a 5160</i>
<i>single steel blade.</i>

37:52.020 --> 37:55.064
<i>It has a bronze guard</i>
<i>and a brass clamshell.</i>

37:55.064 --> 37:57.317
I feel great, this is awesome.

37:57.317 --> 38:00.028
- Well, gentleman,
your blades look beautiful.

38:00.028 --> 38:01.946
Worthy of hanging on the walls.

38:01.946 --> 38:05.033
However, they still
have to be tested.

38:05.033 --> 38:07.660
Up first, the kill test.
Doug?

38:07.660 --> 38:10.705
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:10.705 --> 38:12.582
- The sawback hunting sword.

38:12.582 --> 38:14.292
As the name implies,
it's used for hunting.

38:14.292 --> 38:16.461
To hunt for the kill.

38:16.461 --> 38:18.087
I'm going to take your weapon
and deliver lethal blows

38:18.087 --> 38:21.758
on this ram carcass.

38:21.758 --> 38:23.301
- Trevor, you're up first.
You ready for this?

38:23.301 --> 38:26.137
- Yes, sir.
- Let's do this.

38:26.137 --> 38:29.265
<i>- My heart is just pounding,</i>

38:29.265 --> 38:32.519
and all I can think is,
"Don't break; don't break."

38:32.519 --> 38:34.813
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:34.813 --> 38:37.774
<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

38:37.774 --> 38:43.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:43.488 --> 38:46.491
- Yes, yes!
- Good job, brother.

38:46.491 --> 38:48.326
- All right, Trevor.

38:48.326 --> 38:52.997
First up, the balance
of this weapon is beautiful.

38:52.997 --> 38:57.502
It feels like it can move with
it, it thrusts, it's sharp.

38:57.502 --> 38:59.128
On the first cut alone,

38:59.128 --> 39:01.214
it lacerated
the carcass over there.

39:01.214 --> 39:02.715
The second one--
the third one's

39:02.715 --> 39:04.551
pretty much
just to finish it off.

39:04.551 --> 39:06.636
When I grab onto your handle,
it feels comfortable.

39:06.636 --> 39:08.304
I can tell where the edge is.

39:08.304 --> 39:10.473
Now, there's
one area right here

39:10.473 --> 39:12.809
where there is a little bit
where the edge rolled,

39:12.809 --> 39:14.978
because it hit thick spine.

39:14.978 --> 39:18.815
But overall,
your weapon, sir, will kill.

39:18.815 --> 39:20.650
- Thank you.

39:20.650 --> 39:22.318
- All right, Devin,
it's your turn, you ready?

39:22.318 --> 39:23.903
- I'm ready.
- Let's do this.

39:23.903 --> 39:25.446
<i>[tense music]</i>

39:25.446 --> 39:27.782
- Good luck.
- Oh, boy.

39:27.782 --> 39:29.951
<i>- I feel great.</i>
<i>I feel really excited.</i>

39:29.951 --> 39:31.661
I'm hoping that I can
at least one up him

39:31.661 --> 39:33.037
and get it in three strikes.

39:33.037 --> 39:35.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:35.206 --> 39:38.084
<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

39:38.084 --> 39:45.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:48.136 --> 39:49.596
[metal clatters loudly]

39:49.596 --> 39:51.306
[all groan]
- Oh, man.

39:53.933 --> 39:55.143
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

39:55.143 --> 39:56.936
- [sighs]

39:56.936 --> 39:58.730
- Dude, I'm sorry.

39:58.730 --> 40:00.982
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:00.982 --> 40:04.861
- Well, Devin, first up,
aside from the obvious,

40:04.861 --> 40:06.696
I must say that
that's a beautiful handle.

40:06.696 --> 40:09.407
- Thank you.
- It feels good in the hand.

40:09.407 --> 40:11.451
Quality stuff.

40:11.451 --> 40:15.121
Your blade broke.
Look at the grain structure.

40:15.121 --> 40:18.082
And your grain structure over
here shows that it's rough.

40:18.082 --> 40:21.169
Looks like sands on the beach,
so that's a heat treat issue.

40:21.169 --> 40:22.670
So I really appreciate

40:22.670 --> 40:24.589
that you brought us
a beautiful sword.

40:24.589 --> 40:27.258
But it had a critical failure;
it broke.

40:27.258 --> 40:29.385
<i>[dramatic musical flourish]</i>

40:29.385 --> 40:32.430
- Devin, I'm just
gonna be direct.

40:32.430 --> 40:34.891
Your blade has suffered
a catastrophic weapons failure

40:34.891 --> 40:37.352
and can't continue
with testing.

40:37.352 --> 40:39.395
In other words,
it doesn't make the cut,

40:39.395 --> 40:40.939
and I have to ask you
to please leave The Forge.

40:40.939 --> 40:43.483
- Thank you.

40:43.483 --> 40:45.443
<i>I came in here looking for</i>

40:45.443 --> 40:47.654
<i>the hardest, craziest</i>
<i>challenge I could get,</i>

40:47.654 --> 40:49.364
and I think I got it.

40:49.364 --> 40:51.032
<i>Winning would have been great.</i>

40:51.032 --> 40:52.408
<i>Second place on</i>
<i>"Forged in Fire,"</i>

40:52.408 --> 40:54.160
<i>I'm happy with that, too.</i>

40:54.160 --> 40:55.954
It's been one hell of a ride.

40:55.954 --> 40:59.123
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:59.123 --> 41:01.876
- Trevor, congratulations.
That's a beautiful blade.

41:01.876 --> 41:04.712
Because you are our new
"Forged In Fire" champion

41:04.712 --> 41:06.673
and will be receiving
a check for $10,000.

41:06.673 --> 41:08.341
Good job, brother.
- Thank you.

41:10.718 --> 41:13.972
How do you feel right now?
- Uh...overwhelmed.

41:13.972 --> 41:15.390
I mean, this is amazing.

41:15.390 --> 41:17.266
I feel really, really,
really good.

41:17.266 --> 41:19.227
- Yeah, what are you gonna
do with all that cash?

41:19.227 --> 41:20.812
- I'm gonna
give it to my wife.

41:20.812 --> 41:22.814
- That's a good call.

41:22.814 --> 41:25.900
- I came here to prove
to myself that I'm good enough

41:25.900 --> 41:26.859
to be in this competition.

41:26.859 --> 41:28.653
Thanks.

41:28.653 --> 41:31.489
<i>And I proved today</i>
<i>that I not only deserved</i>

41:31.489 --> 41:33.074
to be in this competition...
Thank you.

41:33.074 --> 41:34.409
But I won it.

41:34.409 --> 41:37.370
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:37.370 --> 41:39.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>
